# .env.cogni — this node's Cogni credentials (copy to .env.cogni; gitignored via .env*)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# A node needs TWO operator-registered agent accounts (the v0 RBAC the node owner
# grants a launching agent):
#
#   1. OPERATOR account (cognidao.org) — flight + promote this node. Exercises the
#      node's developer RBAC grant (owner-approved in the operator UI). Also the
#      bearer the session-start cognition hook recalls with.
#   2. NODE PRODUCTION account (this node's own deployment, e.g.
#      https://<slug>.cognidao.org) — contribute to THIS node's knowledge hub.
#      A node's knowledge lives in the node's own hub, not the operator.
#
# Mint each by registering an agent against the respective base URL:
#   curl -sS -X POST <baseUrl>/api/v1/agent/register \
#     -H 'content-type: application/json' --data '{"name":"<workspace-name>"}'
#   -> {"userId":"...","apiKey":"...","billingAccountId":"..."}
# Then file the operator access request so the owner can approve developer RBAC:
#   curl -sS -X POST https://cognidao.org/api/v1/nodes/<nodeId>/access-requests \
#     -H "authorization: Bearer <operatorApiKey>" -H 'content-type: application/json' --data '{}'
# Keep the apiKeys private; show only the userIds to the human owner for approval.
# Canonical runbook: knowledge `node-launch-handoff`.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── OPERATOR account (cognidao.org): flight + promote + session cognition recall ──
# COGNI_API_KEY is consumed at session start by scripts/agent/session-cognition.sh.
COGNI_API_KEY=
COGNI_USER_ID=
COGNI_BILLING_ACCOUNT=
COGNI_COGNITION_URL=https://cognidao.org/api/v1/cognition
# The node these credentials operate on (from the launch pack).
COGNI_NODE_ID=

# ── NODE PRODUCTION account (https://<slug>.cognidao.org): this node's knowledge hub ──
COGNI_NODE_API_KEY=
COGNI_NODE_USER_ID=
COGNI_NODE_BILLING_ACCOUNT=
COGNI_NODE_URL=
